> s

A GARAGE FRONT

I'm stood in the middle of the field in front of the old aluminium garage door. The door is now open and rolled up into the ceiling.

The inside of the garage is infront of me to the north. The front door of the cottage is over to my west. Further over to my east in the middle of the field is the old gazebo.
> w

> w

COTTAGE FRONT

I'm stood under the rustic little wooden archway that serves as a porch to the cottage. It's still a deceptively large property. Its low, with only one storey plus a little attic space if I remember correctly, but it commands a large surface area.

Facing me northwards is a nauseating lime green door that's seen better days. Along the wall a few yards to my left is a dirty old metallic window.

The garage door is just across the path to my east. The path heading back to the gate is south.
> n

> n

FRONT CORRIDOR

Ok. I put on the face mask and gloves. Here goes...

About an hour and a half has passed. I've managed to get a good majority of the...stuff...off the main corridor walls.

I haven't been into any of the rooms yet. This has taken me long enough. I'm sweating and tired, but I think enough of the smell has gone to walk around the house, for now.

I think I'll leave the facemask on though.

FRONT CORRIDOR

I'm in the front corridor of the cottage. It's kind of gloomy, but lets be honest, that's the least of the problems in here right now. I just have to ignore what remains of the brown smears all over the walls.

The old fashioned beige wallpaper has most definately seen better days. Even before being smeared in shit. The light fittings appear to be disconnected and literally hanging by threads. All in all, there's a general sense of neglect.

And excrement.

The corridor travels directly ahead of me to the north towards the back of the house and to my west towards the dining room.

The outside is back out of the front door to the south.
> n

> n

EAST CORRIDOR

I'm stood in the corridor that runs directly from the front door to the back of house. There's not much light, but I'm able to see a handful of framed pictures adorning the walls.

An exit to the north-east leads to the utility room. South-east is the door to the kitchen. The rear corridor is to the north and the front corridor is to the south.
> se

> se

KITCHEN

I'm in a large, fairly modern looking kitchen. Modern enough that it stands in fair contrast to the rest of the house. It looks like it was installed within the last couple of years at the most.

Stainless steel work surfaces wrap around the the entirety of the room against the walls, only broken in their flow by the entrance, the large fridge freezer and the massive Aga. Above the work surfaces, various utensils and cooking implements hang on hooks

In the centre of the room lies a large wooden bench-styled dining table.

The exit is back through the door to the west.
> open aga

> open aga
Ok the cooker door is open. Looks like there's a tray inside.
> x tray

> x tray
I start to pull the tray out and look at the contents. I jump across the kitchen and scream in absolute horror.

Inside the tray are the decomposing remains of two human thumbs.

What was he doing to himself?!? WHAT WAS HE THINKING?!?
I scream, just because I need to.
> w

> w

EAST CORRIDOR

I'm stood in the corridor that runs directly from the front door to the back of house. There's not much light, but I'm able to see a handful of framed pictures adorning the walls.

An exit to the north-east leads to the utility room. South-east is the door to the kitchen. The rear corridor is to the north and the front corridor is to the south.
> s

> s

FRONT CORRIDOR

I'm in the front corridor of the cottage. It's kind of gloomy, but lets be honest, that's the least of the problems in here right now. I just have to ignore what remains of the brown smears all over the walls.

The old fashioned beige wallpaper has most definately seen better days. Even before being smeared in shit. The light fittings appear to be disconnected and literally hanging by threads. All in all, there's a general sense of neglect.

