> w

> w

A WEST CORRIDOR

I'm in the dingy west corridor of the house. There's not much here other than more ruined wallpaper and cobwebs.

Directly northwards is the rear corridor of the house, whilst the door to the den lies to the northwest. The doors to the dining room and the bathroom are off to the southwest and southeast respectively.

Eastwards leads to the front corridor.
> nw

> nw

DEN

I'm in the den. It's a cosy room. Not particularly big. The walls are a warm shade of crimson. Old dark brown throws line the sofa and armchair. The floor is tiled in a sharp black stone and a large fireplace sits cold and dead in the corner.

There are bottles everywhere. Lots of bottles. I'm talking around maybe fifty. Vodkas, Rums, Bourbons, Whiskeys, Scotches. Some a good few years old. All empty.

Next to the sofa on the north wall is a large book case. Its shelves are full to the brim with tomes on various subjects. Across from the book case in the far corner is a large LCD television. A remote control sits on top.

The room opens up into a new conservatory extension to the west. The door heads back into the corridor to the east.

> take small key

> take small key
Ok, I've taken the key.
> e

> e

A WEST CORRIDOR

I'm in the dingy west corridor of the house. There's not much here other than more ruined wallpaper and cobwebs.

Directly northwards is the rear corridor of the house, whilst the door to the den lies to the northwest. The doors to the dining room and the bathroom are off to the southwest and southeast respectively.

Eastwards leads to the front corridor.
> n

> n

REAR CORRIDOR

I'm in the rear corridor of the house. It's pretty dark and dingy back here but maybe that's for the best.

The west corridor lies, funnily enough, to my west, while the east corridor is eastwards. In the middle of the corridor pointing southwards is the entrance to the office.
> use small key on office door

> use small key on office door
Ok, the office door is unlocked.
> s

> s

OFFICE

I'm stood in a large, cold stone room which appears to be a dubious mix of a study and a workshop.

The rear of the room is dominated by a large mahogany desk sat under the wide northwards facing window. The desk is littered with mounds of paperwork. The surface of the desk itself is utterly hidden. Going through all this stuff is going to take me hours.

A large workbench encompasses the other side of the room. Various woodworking and power tools dominate the area.

Stood at the back of the bench along the wall are a number of wooden sculptures that look to be in various states of completion.

The door back into the corridor is to the north.

> switch on computer

> switch on computer
Ok, I've turned the computer on.
The computer very slowly chugs and whirrs to life. Various screens flick past. The Windows M.E logo comes up (wow this is old) and everything suddenly stops.

After about ten seconds the screen goes bright blue and reems of white text appear on the screen saying things like 'FATAL ERROR', 'DISPLAY ADAPTOR' and 'HARDWARE FAILURE'.

I literally have no idea what any of this means. If Ryan were here he'd probably know what to do.

He's thirteen. It's actually depressing he knows more about this stuff than me.

After a few minutes I decide I'm probably not going to get anywhere with this thing and turn the computer back off.
> x abacus

> x abacus
A wooden counting abacus. It's rough and yet to be varnished. Another of my uncle's various products I imagine. The individual counters must have taken him ages.
> use calender

> use calender
I decide to modify the calender to the correct date. I figure I should.

As I pick up the calender, a yale lock key falls out from the inner tube. I pick it up.
> n

> n

REAR CORRIDOR

I'm in the rear corridor of the house. It's pretty dark and dingy back here but maybe that's for the best.

The west corridor lies, funnily enough, to my west, while the east corridor is eastwards. In the middle of the corridor pointing southwards is the entrance to the office.
> w

> w

A WEST CORRIDOR

I'm in the dingy west corridor of the house. There's not much here other than more ruined wallpaper and cobwebs.

Directly northwards is the rear corridor of the house, whilst the door to the den lies to the northwest. The doors to the dining room and the bathroom are off to the southwest and southeast respectively.

Eastwards leads to the front corridor.
> use yale key on dining room door

> use yale key on dining room door
Ok, the dining room door is unlocked.
> sw

> sw

DINING ROOM

I'm in the dining room. It's a cold, draughty room, uncharacteristic of the rest of the house.

It's a large space, dominated by the georgian table and chairs in the centre. The table is varnished and spotless and already set to receive. Immaculate silver cutlery has been placed for each seat, as well as black dinner mats and tumblers. An antique looking vase stands in the middle of the table.

The only other object in the room is the old bureau against the north wall.

A boarded up window looks out southwards to the front grounds of the house.

The door back into the corridor is east.
> x bureau

> x bureau
The ornate wooden bureau dominates the north wall, almost reaching to the ceiling. It's stood at a perculiar angle.

It's glass cabinets contain various glasses and what appear to be genuine crystal goblets.

The bureau desk has two framed pictures standing on it. One of my grandparents, Dad and Mark's parents and one of me and my family. My two kids, Dave, me.

I miss them.

Why do I have a horrible feeling?...
> push bureau

> push bureau
I gather my strength (what there is of it) and heave myself against the side of the large bureau. I manage to get it to pivot out slightly from the wall.

There's the door to a safe here. It's built directly into the wall at floor level.

How long has this been here?
> x safe

> x safe
It's the door to a safe that's been built directly into the wall. It looks like it was installed recently.

It works on a four digit combination dial.
> set dial to 3367

> set dial to 3367
With a click, the safe unlocks and opens. There's nothing inside.

It's actually some kind of hole.

It's heading into the wall and downward to the north. I can't see the other end...

The smell of something rotten and horrific creeps up the hole towards me.

What the hell???
> switch on torch

> switch on torch
It is already switched on.
> n

> n

CRAWLSPACE

I'm in some kind of makeshift tunnel heading down a slope. The tunnel appears to have been haphazardly dug out. The ground is rough and uneven. The space has been re-enforced with corrugated iron above. I'm on my hands and knees and wondering what the hell I'm doing here right now.

There's a faint patch of light ahead of me northwards. Or I can shuffle southwards back out.

I want to get out of this thing as quickly as possible.
> n

> n

UNDERGROUND ROOM

I'm in a large room underneath the house. I've never seen this room before. I didn't even know it existed. It looks like some kind of basement.

Other than the makeshift crawlspace I've just emerged from, the only other means of entrance to room appears to have been a large wooden hatchway out into the rear grounds of the property. However, the hatchway has been thoroughly boarded up with a multitude of two by fours. The stairs leading up to the hatchway have been demolished. Only the scuffs on the floor left by the struts of the stairs remain.

I don't recall ever seeing a hatchway into a cellar outside the house. I'm guessing the outside section of the hatch was removed and covered in turf.

A small window high up near the ceiling is lighting a small patch of light into the room from ground level.

At the other end of the room is some kind of steel cage, like a jail cell...

...oh, my god.....

> x jail cell

> x jail cell

I...

My first instinct is to run. Run as far away and as fast as I possibly can.

Run home. Just go.

But I can't.

There's a corpse here.

A man. A DEAD FUCKING MAN!

WHY WOULD HE DO THIS?!?

A dead man. Locked in a steel cell. It's around six foot squared. There appears to be no way to open the cell. I think it was constructed around the man while he was here. There appears to be wrist shackles anchored into the walls. Just outside of the cell in the north east corner of the room is a large stack of empty cans of beans.

Sat just outside the cell on the floor are a notebook and a pen.

I want to run. But I can't.

I need to know why.

> x corpse

> x corpse
I don't know...

He's been dead a few weeks, maybe. The flesh is starting to liquify. The flies are doing there thing.

His hair and beard were long. He was wearing dark blue overalls.

He's huddled in the foetal position. Like he was terrified.
> x notebook

> x notebook
The notebook has been fixed to a metal plate which in turn is fixed to a chain across the room from the cell. It only reaches just far enough to the cell so the man could have written in it without being able to bring it any closer.

I think my uncle didn't want the man to have any access to any objects the man could potentially use to harm himself. He wanted him alive.
> read notebook

> read notebook

The first entry is dated 11th January 2012:

"I'm sorry. I'm an idiot. Please let me go. I shouldn't have done what I did. You said you've given me this book to express myself. Well I'm expressing myself. I'M FUCKING SORRY!!!!!! Hand me over to the police, do whatever you want, just please let me go."
13th January 2012:

"He said I'm here because he wants somebody to talk to. He took my clothes and gave me overalls. He said I have to wear these because science can get messy. He said my name is now Julian. He wants me to only respond to Julian. Please somebody help me!!!!!"
28th January 2012:

"I can't keep eating beans. Please. Please give me something else."
29th January 2012:

"He said we are going to take part in frequent conversations. He said if I don't engage thoroughly in these conversations that he will take away my 'privileges'. WHAT FUCKING PRIVILEGES??!??!"
5th February 2012:

"He's been coming down here and asking me about my family. Why I love them, why I named my kids what I did, what I love about my girlfriend. How they make me feel. I screamed at him and he threw a can of beans at my face."
7th February 2012:

"Today he asked me about why I broke in. Why I did what I did. I told him that I'm sorry. He told me never to apologise again or he'd drill a hole into my brain. I told him it's because I'm stupid and I don't know how to do anything else with my life. He asked me what I wanted to be when I was a kid. I told him I wanted to be a policeman."
27th February 2012:

"He asked me about my beliefs. I told him I didn't really have any. He asked me if I believe people have a destiny, or a script. I said I don't know. He didn't like that. He said it was a default answer. I need to work on my templates?!?!?
3rd March 2012:

"He tried explaining all this shit to me today about the logical absolutes, or something like that. How something is what it is, and not not what it is. How there's no middle. He wants me to talk back to him about this stuff but I DON'T FUCKING UNDERSTAND. Then has asked me if I spoke Chinese?!? He got really angry when I said no. FUCK HIM!!!!!!!!
5th March 2012:

"So I asked the cunt a question. I asked him why 'Julian'. He got so angry he throw a gallon of petrol over me and threatened to set me on fire. I told him if he does that, we won't be able to have our conversations. I've got him by the fucking balls. He started crying and told me something about a girl called Andrea and how she was barren, but Julian was always her favourite name. Like I give a shit you psychotic prick.
6th March 2012:

"I found white bits in my beans today. I think he's putting something in there."
7th April:

"My girlfriend came to visit. She let me watch her dance naked. Then he came and hit me for making a mess. "
April:

"God told me about how nothing is really real today. He said he read things about computers and how we are brains in jars, except not real jars. Computer jars. How we are only a story."
April 1st:

"God told me he has visions. They started when he got ill. I said God doesn't get ill. My daughter was sat in the corner and she laughed."
November:

"He told me about his dreams. About his niece and her family. He said everything is a cycle. It always loops. Begins and Ends. He told me those voices in our head that get us to do things are from outside. Sometimes we can ignore them but mostly we don't. He told me about the photo she puts back at the end. She always cries. She knows i'ts the end. We all sleep at the end. Just like everything else. He told me she'll read this.

Try not to be scared."
Whh,,,,,

What?!?....

What does he mean? How could....

