GROUNDS

I'm stood in the green, dry, muddy grounds of my uncle's cottage. The place looks remarkably well kept, considering its age.

The drive runs up to the garage to the north. There is also a little path leading off to the west towards the front door of the house. The path back to the train station heads past the rusty old gate to the south.
