My phone starts ringing.

Oh my god it's David. I answer,

"Hi honey, you ok?"
His voice makes me cry.

"Yes, I'm fine, " I reply, "I'm...I just miss you baby. "

" Are the boys ok? "
" Yeah they're fine. Ryan's team won the semi-final match. They're in the final. "
I laugh and sob. " Ha ha, fantastic. Tell them I love them ok? "
"Will do. You just hang in there. We'll have yo-"

The phone cuts out.

PATH

I'm walking up the steep path, heading up towards the top of the valley. The forest canopy covers the path clearing in a blanket of shade, yet the yellow dusk light is still just about strong enough to illuminate the way before the darkness truly sets in.

It's odd. I usually feel threatened walking by myself in places like this. Today I feel relaxed. Almost serene.

Anyway, It's an enjoyable walk but there's nothing much here apart from trees and mud. Onwards and upwards.

The path continues up the hill to the west. The train station is back down the hill to the east.
> e

> e

PLATFORM

No, no, please. I know this is stupid. It's probably all just nonsense, but I can't get what that man wrote out of my head. He knew...

I just have a bad feeling.

Please don't do this....
